    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02350.001.jpg" type="recto"/>

            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">400 Fifth Avenue</name>
                    <date when="1890-10-12">Oct 12. 90<ptr target="loc.02350_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Whitman&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>On return from Washington last night found your good letter.</p>

            <p>Of course you will have a chance to say your say on the 21st<ptr target="loc.02350_n2"/> and the more you say the
                better&#8212;What you propose is apt and beautiful</p>

            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02350.002.jpg" type="verso"/>

            <p>but you will think of more.</p>

            <p>The occasion, the climate, the subtle something that gives to an audience a
                personality that dominates speakers and hearers&#8212;all these will determine what
                Walt Whitman has to say.&#8212;</p>

            <p>I hope the night will be good&#8212;that</p>

            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02350.003.jpg" type="recto"/>

            <p>you will be in unusual health and spirits, and that you will be satisfied</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>With your friend</salute>
                <signed>R.G. Ingersoll</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.02350.004.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc.02350.005.jpg" type="recto"/>
        </body>
